===from:Amy Metzger
===email:ptflute@bellsouth.net
===date:Mon Sep  1 17:25:55 2003
===subject:Witches...
===message:Warning: LONG...
What I admire most about the Puritans is their desire and effort to be "pure" (no pun intended).  The telling of the truth was very important (as a value) and this caused some of the accused to go to their deaths rather than "admit" guilt they didn't have.  Also, it was probably one of the reasons people were so apt to believe the children.   Their biggest hangup was probably the fact that they didn't know how to explain the "afflictions"  and so they fell to their belief in Satan and Satan's ability to cause afflictions.  They also were of the opinion that bad things were a result of Satan working through people.  Apparently there really were witches (or at least people who "conjured" things and practiced witchcraft somehow) but whether they were really effective or just some kind of mumbo jumbo is unknown.  
Why the hysteria?  Partly because they didn't have an explanation and partly because there were so many involved.  The collaboration between the accusers and the "afflicted" girls fueled the fire that led to the hysteria.  If one says it is happening, or even two, there can be quite a lot of doubt, but not when so many all seemed to be affected.  

=========yorg=========
===from:Patricia Shepard
===date:Mon Sep  1 18:36:36 2003
===subject:Witches in Americas
===message:The thing I most admired about the Puritans was the way they took care of each other.  If someone was old, sick or disabled they were taken care of.  Although they had great compassion toward other Puritans, they seemed to have none for anyone who had different beliefs from them. They were certainly complex people to have so much compassion for their own, but so little tolerance and compassion for anyone whose beliefs were different. There probably were some people indulging in some sort of superstitution. I think the Puritans reacted the way they did because of all the uncertainty and stress they had to be living with at the time.  The people accused of witchcraft were scapegoats for other things going on that could not be concretely dealt with such as being attacked by Indians, am I destined for heaven or hell?, etc.
=========yorg=========
