===message:It takes true conviction to be willing to relocate in a new country, and the Puritans proved that they indeed had a strong conviction when it came to their religion.  But the extent they went to in order to establish christianity is shameful on many levels.  After settling in America and establishing Christianity, they forgot the main reason they left Europe, which was to practice a religion of their choice without being pursecuted.  Here we find the Puritans having no tolerance for any other religion, fighting the Native Americans over land that rightfully is theirs, and pursecuting women who they beleive to be witches.  It is often said that the most religious people can be the biggest "hell raisers".  This phrase certainly describes the Puritans.  


