===subject:Witches in the American Immagination
===message:What I admire most about the Puritans was their belief of the origin sin that Jesus Christ was recognized as the Son of God and gave His life for the atonement of our sins. I also admire the fact that the followers were required to read and study the Bible for themselves.
On the other hand, I believe if the followers truly studied their Bible, church membership would not be predicated upon an outward demonstration to prove if they were saved. How hypocritical!
I cannot unequivocally state that I believe that there were or were not any witches in Salem. The jury is still out. I believe that there was mass hysteria because people have always feared the unknown. One wants to always attribute an explanation for any type of misfortune. When there is no explanation, one is made up and has snow ball effect.
