===from:Judy Nunnally
===email:jnunnally2@aol.com
===date:Sun Oct 26 20:50:35 2003
===subject:Witches in the American Imagination
===message:The most admirable quality, and I believe their worst,was their blind faith in their chosen religious leaders.  When a group of people stand by and watch as helpless men and women are execute in the cruelest fashion, it demeans all their pious protestations of belief in any kind of God.  I think that the driving force behind these attrocities was greed and jealousy.  This is evident in the biblical commandments that they violated.  Namely "Thou shalt not bear false witness", "Thou shalt not covet", and the formost of these, "Thou shalt not kill".  There is no such thing as witches.  Fear is a great motivator.
